From: Nexus Q Reloaded Project <nexusq@localhost>
Subject: [PATCH] mfd: twl-core: register clock mfd cell for TWL6030 too

The clk-twl driver handles clk32kg/clk32kaudio for both TWL6030 and
TWL6032 (register layout is identical: CFG_TRANS base 0x8C/0x8F), but
twl-core only instantiated the clock cell for TWL6032. The Nexus Q
(steelhead) BCM4330 WiFi/BT needs clk32kaudio as its sleep clock
(see board-steelhead-wifi.c in the AOSP android-omap-steelhead kernel),
so register the cell for the whole 6030 class.

--- a/drivers/mfd/twl-core.c
+++ b/drivers/mfd/twl-core.c
@@ -861,7 +861,7 @@ twl_probe(struct i2c_client *client)
 		}
 	}
 
-	if (id->driver_data == (TWL6030_CLASS | TWL6032_SUBCLASS)) {
+	if (twl_class_is_6030()) {
 		status = devm_mfd_add_devices(&client->dev,
 					      PLATFORM_DEVID_NONE,
 					      twl6032_cells,
